install.packages('highcharter')
Error in install.packages : Updating loaded packages

We will make a US map of the arrests. This is an old data set from 1973! From the data description:

This data set contains statistics, in arrests per 100,000 residents for assault, murder, and rape in each of the 50 US states in 1973. Also given is the percent of the population living in urban areas.

data("USArrests", package = "datasets")
head(USArrests)

We will combine this data set with the US map using a variable woe-name which is missing from this data set. But as it turns out, this can be extracted from the row names of this dat aset

USArrests2 <- dplyr::mutate(USArrests, `woe-name` = rownames(USArrests))

head(USArrests2)
NA
hcmap(map = "countries/us/us-all", 
      data = USArrests2,
      joinBy = "woe-name",
      value = "Murder",
      name = "Murder Rate per 100,000",
      download_map_data = TRUE)

We will map US unemployment data. This is a granual data at the county level.


data(unemployment)

head(unemployment)

Now lets make a map. Note that we are providing hcmap() a map of the US and then the unemployment data. These two data sets are merged using joinBy argument.


hcmap(map = "countries/us/us-all-all", #highcharter will download this from highcharts server
      data = unemployment, # This is what we provide
      name = "Unemployment",
      value = "value",
      joinBy = c("hc-key", "code"), # The code is the county code
      borderColor = "transparent") %>%
  hc_colorAxis(dataClasses = color_classes(c(seq(0, 10, by = 2), 50))) %>% 
  hc_legend(layout = "vertical", align = "right",
            floating = TRUE, valueDecimals = 0, valueSuffix = "%")

if(require("mapproj") && require("ggplot2")) {
  crimes <- data.frame(state = tolower(rownames(USArrests)), USArrests)
  p <- ggplot(crimes, aes(fill = UrbanPop, map_id = state)) +
    geom_map(map = fifty_states) +
    expand_limits(x = fifty_states$long, y = fifty_states$lat) +
    coord_map()
 p
 # Add bounding boxes for Alaska and Hawaii
 p + fifty_states_inset_boxes()
}
